It's incredible how easily my mood is influenced by music XD Nickelbacks "Gotta Be Somebody" makes me super happy and stuff.

23 Days till metro practice starts!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! Secret chess character FTW.

I'm being academically responsible! Going to all my classes, doing all my stuff, i feel like I'm getting on the right track ^_^ Which is awesome, I'm glad that I finally feel like I'm doing everything right...well, not everything, but at least I feel less like a failure.

Fire show practice is fun, my arms hurt every wednesday morning but its super worth it. I have Asia's poi to play with during the week, they're a lot more effective then my sock poi! I hope I get to light up soon..=D

Ummm, let's see, laura and vic and me are joining in a new RPG on teusdays based on Dune! Tomorrow is dune mini series watching day to get ready, i'm excited. I hear the mini series is 100 times better then the movie, so I'm sure it'll be pretty good ^_^

Someone stole my laundry basket! It was alone in the laundry room between 2 am and 7 am, and it was GONE! Who steals a laundry basket?!?! Now I'm paranoid about theft, I'm not bitter about it anymore (that only lasted like an hour lol), I just need something to put my dirty clothes in....i dont wanna have to buy a new basket, maybe a storage bin? yeah, that could work.

The chess/masque/star party saturday was AMAZING, meeting everyone was so awesome. I can tell this is going to be a good group ^_^ I wish I could've gone to celebrate tylers b-day, but c'est la vie, I had made plans for that night. In any case, I hope he had a fun time =)

<3,
Liz

Studying biology makes me feel like a failure =P I hates it SO MUCH......arrghhhh.........but i hate to learn it for this stupid damn class I'm taking. I need the grade. So...yeah. Back to <strike>hating life</strike> studying.

<3,
Liz
With every up, there is a down.

I'm in the chess match this year!!!!

SO excited for practices. See everyone sooooon :-DDD

<3,
Liz

When I hear a song I like, I don't favorite it and listen to it once in a while. Oh no. I run it into the GROUND. For WEEKS, I'll sing it, until I get sick of it one day and never want to hear it again. It's like a sickness. Songs grab at me until I hear them enough to have every note memorized.

Songs I have somehow not yet managed to get tired of yet INCLUDE: Sexy Naughty Bitchy, Gives you Hell, anything by Paramore and Love me Dead.

Biology is kicking my ass =P I'm good at math, good at almost anything in school, but this is my one weakness. Week 2 and I think I need a tutor. It makes me feel a little dumb, but I know that it's better to get help early.

It looks like the Rikku cosplay actually might happen by metro =DDDD It'll be Rikku frmo FF X, not FF XII, so I don't have to buy a wig. Medium length blonde hair finally comes in handy for a cospaly! If I get the money, I know who I want to make it for me, and it'll look super cute.

No word from Battle Con yet! I sent in my pics/info for a shot at being in their fan girls of anime calendar (Your supposed to send a pic, your age, and what character you want to portray, I said misa misa from death note ^_^). I'm sure I'll hear back from them in like 3 months when chess mania has taken over (assuming i get in *crosses fingers and prays*) and I've forgotten all about battle con. I do hope I get in though, it sounds fun and I'd love to have a calendar to show my grandkids to say 'See, this wrinkled lady WAS hot back in the day! Told ya!'. Lol jk. But I am hoping to get in.

When I go to book and music stores, I get recognized a lot from Metro. This isn't related to anything, i just think its kind of cool and fun, Ive made a few awesome acquaintences this way.

Dinner at steak and shake with chess crew made me realize how much I miss everyone. **makes mental note to hang out with and keep in touch with everyone more **

<3,
Liz

Chess auditions yesterday were AH-MAZING =DDD It was so nice seeing everyone, I hope that things work out this year!!! I want clare and gally and asuka, but I'd be happy with anything really, just being a part of the experience is awesome. Steak and shake afterwards was very fun times, but everything hurts, mostly from hitting myself all over with the fire show balls-on-chains (dont remember name lol). If I can find a ride up to largo on teusdays from USF, I am definitely going out there to learn to spin fire. On an unrelated note, I love my sweet awesome boyfriend.

<3,
Liz

I named 50 US states in 10 minutes
With maddies help of course =) Auditions tomorrow! Yaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaay!
Battle Con picture taking tiem with maddie and laura was epic fun. I'm doing well, just wanted to post a couple cute . Will make a real update later. ^_^. <3, Liz
Merry early christmas and happy holidays to all =)
Calling all girls and people who love cute adorable little animals: http://www.dailypuppy.com/ Go there now. I melted. =DDD

Holidays.....

Merry early christmas to all. May your holidays be as good as I hope tomorrow ends up being.

A guy walked up to a yo - yo salesman, and asked, how's life?

The yo - yo salesman said,

"Oh, it has its ups and downs."

That's kinda how my week has been going.

Tomorrow should be UP UP UP though!! ^_^ I'm excited.

No more school, no more books, no more teachers dirty looks! WHOOO! Just one e - mailed exam to turn in and I am home FREE (for now anyway ^_^) I just got back from my psych exam and I'm so done with that class.

Job hunting is still sucky, but whatevs, it'll happen soon, I just have to keep trying. I'll make things work in the mean time.

For the third time in my life, metro falls training has gotten me through a bike accident. i was actually pretty proud of myself, instead of panicking, i felt zero fear and just readied myself for impact. All i got was a huge, fearsome looking scrape on my right knee, and that was a pretty decent spill onto dusty concrete. For me, stage combat training doubles as SURVIVAL training. Lol.

 I think.....I'm just not meant to ride a bike. This ones front wheel pops off, the basket came off (...after i dropped the bike...), the thing covering the chain comes undone and needs to be pushed back into place, and now the chain came off. This bike sounds so broken and such when i describe its quirks, but I've become attached. That whole chain coming off thing is a problem, though, since I can't put it back on with the protective chain cover still attached to my bike.

Zack and Miri Make a Porno is AH-mazing. Go see it if you haven't.

I love Garion. Just sayin.

So close to christmas, I'm excited =D

You Are A: Kitten!

Cute as can be, kittens are playful, mischevious, and ever-curious. Like you, kittens hate getting wet. Kittens are often loving, but are known to scratch or bite when annoyed. These adorable animals are the most popular pets in the United States--37% of American households have at least one cat. Whether it is your gentle purr or your disarming appearance, you make a wonderful kitten.

You were almost a: Squirrel or a Monkey
You are least like a: Turtle or a BunnyWhat Cute Animal Are You?
And thank you to everyone who commented in or even just read my last post, it helped a lot ^_^

I'm worried about grades.....arghhh.......especially because I'm on scholarship, I hate this feeling of apprehension. I'm not even sure college is right for me right now, I don't know what i want to do with my life! Who says that a college degree is ZOMGNECESSARY for a decent life? There are so many things you can do that dont need a degree. Dont get me wrong, there's a lot that you absolutely need a degree for, doctors, lawyers, engineers......I dont know, I just feel like I'm wasting time here in college with no direction. I wish I had taken a year off to figure out what i wanted to DO with my college life. Or if i even wanted to do a career that NEEDED a degree.

I guess I just want to feel like if I'm in college, I want to be working towards a goal that I need college for. Like I'm going somewhere with my degree. Which I definitely do not feel right now. I feel like I'm just wasting time and money taking classes like philosophy and english when I could be at a job, making money, and figuring out what I want to do with my life. I want to be in college going somewhere, not because it's what I'm "supposed" to do. My whole family is college-crazy, I imagine that I'd be DISOWNED if I wasn't here.

I'll figure it out.

Watching metrocon tributes makes me miss all of my metro family <3<3<3<3<3

Katie's video to the nickelback song makes me cry every time ::shakes fist::

I came down with the DEATH PLAGUE yesterday, which kinda sucked while eating thanksgiving meal. Throatache, headache, fever, you name it, i probably have it as a symptom lol. But I can't be depressed. Why? Garion skipped his families thanksgiving meal to stay and bring me orange juice, medicine, and hugs. I tried to get him to leave me and see his family, but he wouldn't go when I was feeling like death. I'm blessed ^_^ 

So even in shitty health, I have things to be thankful for. Friends, family, self sacraficing and amazing boyfriend, everything. Happy thanksgiving everyone! =) Hope there was lots of turkey and pie to go around. I know my throat will never be too sore for my grandmothers pumpkin pie, or my dads brined turkey, or moms mashed potatoes.

I want to be a disney princess when I grow up =DDD

That's what I've been doing whenever I get on the internet for the last two days or so lol. Looking up height requirements (im princess height! yay!), audition tips, anectdotes, stories, etc.

That is all.

Ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha

Things and stuff, junk and life. Good times.

Not really.

But whatever.

Nothing I can do about it, right?

IDK. We'll see I guess. We'll see.

Status: with laura in a pit of wallow playing heroscape with cris vic and a guy I dont know and eating our weight in pizza and pepsi. Hilarious games and one liners, shittactular week.

Good times? YOU be the judge!

Too cute not to put here. Tomorrows gonna be an interesting day. Instead of writing bad stuff, I'll write the good that came out of tonight and say that I love my friends to pieces. Even the ones I don't see much, like the LJ and metro ppl who I dont get to hang out with enough. Tonight made me realize how important friends can really be sometimes.

::smile::

I just know that someone's going to get a patented Liz tongue lashing. I'm betting that since mostly chesss and masque ppl know me on this LJ, they've never seen me get mad or discouraged or anything. They've read about it on LJ,m but never SEEN it. I don't tell people when I'm upset because I like to be a positive person. And I am most of the time. I'm pretty happy generally, this has just been kind of a shitty wek for me in a lot of ways. That's OK, its life and it happens to everyone.

But..........there are limits, even for me, I have those points where ENOUGH IS ENOUGH. I'm like a rocket ship, it takes a LOT to get me mad enough to want to punch someone but once I get there, it's extreme. I just don't know what I'm going to do when I see this person. Being friendly is out of the question, and if I let loose talking about how I feel about them and what they do it could get ugly. Oh well. Let the ugly begin =)

I was in such a good mood, me/katie/vic/laura/maddie chilling at lunch, talking about the characters we heard at the panel, then chilling in maddies dorm watching AMVs, today was cool. Today was fun. WAS.

Then I walked into Biology of Humans, and all of that died.

I hate this class. I hate it. I never want to study science ever again. This class is crushing my soul as we speak. I'm thinking of withdrawing.

This sucks.

SUPER fun day.

Most mediocre night i've ever had, when you average out everything. Fun game, nice talking to people, sucky downtime, seeing videos. Meh.

I need necro.

PLZ happy anime con, take me away! ^_^

Hey everyone!

Just posting to say how much I love youtube. I could look on there all day at AMVS! I *love* the YuRiPa video to "Sexy, Naughty, Bitchy" by Tata Young. Srsly, its so ah-dorable. Me/laura/maddie have been joking so long about being Rikku (me!) Yuna (laura) and Paine (maddie). Joined with Squall (cris) and Rinoa (vic) nothing can stand in our way to defeating evil!

Back to doing stuff.

Cause, that IS what we do in this house.

Stuff.

<3

Ahhhhhhhhhhh!

THREE days till necro!

I am so pumped.

Srsly.

Chess match panel FTW.

The hours in the gym are paying off, i feel stronger and more flexible already.

Two days ago, my boyfriend and I celebrated our one year anniversary together. It was awesome. ^_^ I love him.

Mmmm, is there any month better then october? I think not. I can smell the fall air, chess characters are revealed, halloween, my anniversary, USF places are hiring....its great. 

I love geometry wars. And corcissone (sp? no way i spelled that right :-P). Those little games that come with the Xbox are so fun. 

Not fun enough to convince me of its superiority to Sony, but fun.

Dr. Horrible is infectious.

I've been humming the songs all day.

At least it's better then having the duck tales theme stuck in my head.

"Life is like a hurricane, here in duckberg, lasers racecars aeroplanes, it's a duck blur, you might solve a mystery, or rewrite HISTORY, Duck tales! Woo Hoo!"

That song tormented me for DAYS after watching that episode of the Nostalgia Critic.

OH, and the Angry Video Game Nerd? So funny =DDD

AHHHHHH!

I can't WAIT for necronomicon this year!!!

^_^ SO excited.

Gym today will help get the energy out and the fitness built up!

I also have no idea what to bring to necronomicon for cosplay......I want to bring Serenity, but have no hotel room to stash it in. I might anyway, I *love* that costume and have almost no pictures of me in it. Oh, so Laura and I have a very special surprise for everyone at the Metrocon panel on saturday at necro! It's going to be so awesome. If Maddie and Vic can get theirs, they will be in on it too!

::sigh::

Life is good, then its bad, then its good again. Then its bad again. Then your whole dorm gets sick, and you get sick from something else but dont wanna see a doctor cause you hate doctors and dont want to feel weak or like your giving up or what if something seriously wrong.

But then theres roleplaying and movies and good times with friends and an improving relationship.

Late + tired + sick VS life is actually going well

I think I'll take it :-)

<3

Life at USF is going really well. I hit the gym 2 or 3 times a week, classes are ok, social life is going rather well (tho i havent done the wild parties thing yet, its mostly hanging out and doing stuff with friends, more chill).

All the girls here are like six feet tall.

I'm so used to being the tall one, now more often then not I'm the smallest one on the elevator, or in the room.....it's weird, but its interesting. I've always been the thinnest, I'm not used to being one of the shortest. I am only 5'7" though, normal height for girls goes up to 6'4".

House Bunny is really funny. Surprisingly so. The girl who played shelley was actually doing the dumb blonde thing in a funny, cute way. I enjoyed it, so did the guys that me, jessica, and laura conned into seeing it with us >:-). Actually, we were all hanging out and just asked nicely if everyone wouldnt mind seeing house bunny, but I like the word conned better. More of an evil connotation. Mwhahaha!

I love the feeling of having new tone, new strength. It's nice. I love the crew machine, my arms arent so scrawny anymore. The fish game is totally epic. Its hard to explain.

I've taken up an RP, Mechton or something like that. I'm a Wuxian trooper, and I never knew how cool tabletop games were! Every thursday is girls night at armada games with me, laura, and vic, and we always see james and patrick there, so if anyones in the neighborhood at that time they should come hang out. It is super fun times. We play the most retarted looking games, like "Hey, thats my fish!" which evolved into me, laura, vic, and james yelling at each other stuff like "I'm not fucking around with these fucking fish!!!!". Oh, what we do to kids games.....

I'm so happy for my boyfriend! He has a job now, and a good one, so that's really cool. Our one year anniversary is in about three weeks, i still have no idea what to get him! Ahhhhh!

Metro season needs to start again. I had to write a memoir, and I wrote about metro, and it made me miss everyone all over again <3<3<3

Ttyl,
Liz

P.S. - http://www.cracked.com/ is ah-mazing.

Dear Makers of Fantastic Contraption:

Your game? It rules. Seriously. But your last few levels?

...hatred. Nothing but hatred. Can we end this love hate relationship, and be friends again? We can work through it together. Specifically level 'Back and Forth'.

Yours,
Liz

So tonight, HAVOC is taking pictures and stuff at the Imax dark knight premeir, and all sorts of coolness.

I should be excited, but I'm kind of dreading it. There has been SO MUCH DRAMA, and its been handled so unprofessionally, that the evening is going to be.....akward, uncomfortable, and probably depressing.

I am excited about getting back into my catwoman costume though. And to see tex, cris, patrick, and vic. If I can avoid the people who are causing the grief, this is going to be one hell of a fun night.

James's b-day on saturday! Still don't know what I'm going to get him. Maddie, Laura, and I are pooling moneys for a gift. We'll see :)

I missed calass cause I was so late, it wasnt even worth trying to get there. Made it to all my other classes, though. So I'm learning how to handle things around here.

Playing devils advocate in Acquisition of Knowledge class.

It's going to be an interesting year.

:)

:-P

So college is cool, but kind of boring since classes and clubs and whatnot havent started up yet. Ive been going to the week of welcome events, and theyve been ok, but life here in the USF dorms is still kind of slow. Especially in an all girls dorm, which is interesting to say the least. Id rather be in a co-ed dorm, itll be much much more relaxed, i think. All girls dorm isnt that friendly, at east my floor. Im hoping this wil change by teh end of next week, when life at USF starts going forward. FOr now, its all straightening out school issues and doing stuff.

Meh.

- Liz
